{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17506857","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17506857"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:47:29+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:47:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2578"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2578","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2578"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.18,0.16,0.07,0.49,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2578"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111717"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2578","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2578"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2578"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93785"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"13"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"1044"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4962"},{"type":"tags","id":"4964"},{"type":"tags","id":"4965"},{"type":"tags","id":"9644"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2705"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2715"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2841"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6906"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27077"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43861"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111717","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/111717"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 23-year-old man presents to his General Practitioner with an eight week history of fatigue and dyspnoea on exertion. He has no other symptoms and in particular, no gastrointestinal symptoms such as dark stools. His medical history consists of asthma, which is well controlled with PRN salbutamol. He has no significant family medical history. On examination he is pale and the doctor is concerned he may be anaemic and arranges the following investigations with results below:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHb 88 g/L (135-175)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMCV 76.6 fl (80.0-98.0)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMCH 26.8 pg (27.0-33.0)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPlatelets 295 x10^9/L (150-450)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWCC 8.91 (4.00-11.00)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFerritin 18 ug/L (30-300)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EActive B12 417 pmol/L (150-850)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFolate 10 (7-40)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Peptic ulcer disease","Pernicious anaemia","Alcohol abuse","Coeliac disease","Bowel cancer"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient\u0027s symptoms are most likely explained by his iron deficiency anaemia. In the absence of any other symptoms, he may well have \u003Cstrong\u003Ecoeliac disease \u003C/strong\u003Eto explain the duodenal malabsorption of iron. This causes a microcytic hypochromic blood film. This should be further investigated with coeliac disease antibodies and referral to gastroenterology for endoscopy and biopsy. Although folate and B12 are absorbed in the small bowel and deficiencies might be expected in coeliac disease, folate stores can take several months to deplete and B12 can take several years to deplete. About 20% of patients with coeliac disease do not have any symptoms, in particular, no gastrointestinal symptoms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPeptic ulcer disease\u003C/strong\u003E may cause anaemia from gastrointestinal blood loss. This would be an iron deficiency anaemia, with a microcytic hypochromic picture. However his age, lack of precipitating factors (such as steroids/NSAIDs) and lack of melaena make this diagnosis less likely.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPernicious anaemia\u003C/strong\u003E tends to affect the elderly, and serum B12 is not deficient as would be expected in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAlcohol abuse\u003C/strong\u003E causes a macrocytic anaemia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBowel cancer\u003C/strong\u003E is extremely unlikely in a man of this age without a hereditary syndrome such as the Lynch syndrome or familial adenomatous polyposis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Coeliac disease can present with iron deficiency anaemia even in the absence of gastrointestinal symptoms."],"references":["Balaban DV, Popp A, Ionita Radu F, Jinga M. Hematologic Manifestations in Celiac Disease-A Practical Review. Medicina (Kaunas). 2019 Jul 15;55(7):373. doi: 10.3390/medicina55070373. PMID: 31311098; PMCID: PMC6681208. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31311098/","Lindfors K, Ciacci C, Kurppa K, Lundin KEA, Makharia GK, Mearin ML, Murray JA, Verdu EF, Kaukinen K. Coeliac disease. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2019 Jan 10;5(1):3. doi: 10.1038/s41572-018-0054-z. PMID: 30631077. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30631077/","Walker MM, Ludvigsson JF, Sanders DS. Coeliac disease: review of diagnosis and management. Med J Aust. 2017 Aug 21;207(4):173-178. doi: 10.5694/mja16.00788. PMID: 28814219. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28814219/","Rubio-Tapia A, Hill ID, Semrad C, Kelly CP, Greer KB, Limketkai BN, Lebwohl B. American College of Gastroenterology Guidelines Update: Diagnosis and Management of Celiac Disease. Am J Gastroenterol. 2023 Jan 1;118(1):59-76. doi: 10.14309/ajg.0000000000002075. Epub 2022 Sep 21. Erratum in: Am J Gastroenterol. 2024 Jul 1;119(7):1441. doi: 10.14309/ajg.0000000000002210. PMID: 36602836. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/36602836/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93785"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2578"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93785","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/93785"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-08-19T15:50:30+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-19T15:50:30+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2578"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111717"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"13","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/13"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\ude78","name":"Haematology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:44+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"dat